From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: diaaney <av6cts@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 07:33:09 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] rapier - 1.8 combat: forceHeldSlot on sword blockhit so
 client resyncs BLOCKS_ATTACKS

user reports after respawn the server-side slowdown + damage reduction
still apply (so server state is correct), but the client does not
render the shield pose. this means the client's copy of the held sword
is missing the BLOCKS_ATTACKS component. forceHeldSlot triggers a
slot update packet via ItemStack.STREAM_CODEC which goes through our
force-inject encoder, guaranteeing the client receives an item with
BLOCKS_ATTACKS in its patch.

diff --git a/net/minecraft/world/item/Item.java b/net/minecraft/world/item/Item.java
index e4fdb74675e8b0955bdbb43a5d79b0cfc3a562e0..3371b91339ca5f2e4917b190f9e85d431d802ec4 100644
--- a/net/minecraft/world/item/Item.java
+++ b/net/minecraft/world/item/Item.java
@@ -197,12 +197,15 @@ public class Item implements FeatureElement, ItemLike {
                         return InteractionResult.PASS;
                     }
                 }
-                // rapier - 1.8 combat: for swords, stop first then start. the explicit false->true transition forces the IS_USING entity-data flag to broadcast. without this, after respawn the server can have a stuck stale flag=true while the client's LocalPlayer believes flag=false, so startUsingItem becomes a no-op broadcast-wise and the blockhit pose never renders.
+                // rapier - 1.8 combat: for swords, (1) stop first to force the IS_USING entity-data flag to broadcast a transition, (2) startUsingItem with forceUpdate=true, and (3) resend the held slot so the client's copy of the sword reliably has the BLOCKS_ATTACKS component. without (3), after a respawn the client's LocalPlayer may hold a sword ItemStack whose component got dropped somewhere in the respawn/inventory transfer, and the client-side renderer refuses to play the BLOCK animation even though the server state (slowdown, damage reduction) is correct.
                 if (itemInHand.is(net.minecraft.tags.ItemTags.SWORDS)) {
                     if (player.isUsingItem()) {
                         player.stopUsingItem();
                     }
                     player.startUsingItem(hand, true);
+                    if (player instanceof net.minecraft.server.level.ServerPlayer rapierServerPlayer) {
+                        rapierServerPlayer.containerMenu.forceHeldSlot(hand);
+                    }
                 } else {
                     player.startUsingItem(hand);
                 }
